Package: msaVariant
Type: Package
Title: Clinical-Genetics Multiple Sequence Alignment Visualisation with
        Variant Overlay
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Your", "Name", email = "you@example.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Guangchuang", "Yu", role = "ctb",
           comment = "ggmsa, on which this package builds"))
Description: Extends 'ggmsa' with annotation layers for clinical and
    population genetics. Provides ggplot2 'geom_*' layers that paint
    user-supplied variants and per-residue annotation tracks
    directly onto a multiple sequence alignment, together with
    per-column conservation scoring and protein domain tracks.
    Designed for variant-of-uncertain-significance interpretation,
    rare-disease gene discovery, and expert-panel curation
    workflows. Users supply their own MSA (FASTA) and variant table;
    the package computes conservation from the alignment and
    overlays whatever annotation data the user brings via a generic
    track layer.
